From: WaveCrux Pro capture pipeline
Subject: [PATCH] Add `aresetn` (active-low) to the FST dump (axi_register)

Sibling of `forencich_aresetn_dump.patch` (which targets `tb/axi_ram/`)
— same idea, retargeted at the `axi_register` testbench. The Pro
`Axi4FullDecoder` requires an `aresetn` binding (active-low synchronous
reset). Forencich's testbenches drive `rst` active-high. We expose the
inverted reset in the same testbench-side dump scope so the FST carries
the signal natively — no DUT modification, no decoder change.

Apply with `patch -p1` from inside `verilog-axi/tb/axi_register/`:

    patch -p1 < forencich_axi_register_aresetn_dump.patch

Tested against `alexforencich/verilog-axi` commit
`516bd5dadc3365b7f9e225d2af8fe0b8d804fe53`.

---
 iverilog_dump.v | 4 +++-
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/iverilog_dump.v b/iverilog_dump.v
--- a/iverilog_dump.v
+++ b/iverilog_dump.v
@@ -1,6 +1,8 @@
 module iverilog_dump();
+wire aresetn = !axi_register.rst;
 initial begin
     $dumpfile("axi_register.fst");
     $dumpvars(0, axi_register);
+    $dumpvars(0, iverilog_dump.aresetn);
 end
 endmodule
